gomodel:SYNGO_2521  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: This study shows that DRD1 modulates synaptic transmission via postsynaptic modulation of cell excitability via modulation of NMDARs and AMPARs.\n\nNote: the high level term 'postsynaptic modulation of chemical synaptic transmission (GO:0099170)' was selected because the underlying mechanism of increased NTR responses is not explained. Beware: the term 'regulation of postsynaptic neurotransmitter receptor activity (GO:0098962)' was note selected because reserved for proteins that modulate the intrinsic channel properties of NTRs.. Experimental description: \"ale Sprague Dawley rats (Charles River Laboratories, Wilmington, MA) were maintained on a 12 hr...\"" ;
